details.purpose: To record details about the nutrients that are consumed in the largest quantities.
details.use:
Use to record details about the nutrients that are consumed in the largest quantities.
This archetype has been designed to be used within the 'Details' SLOT in the OBSERVATION.dietary_nutrients archetype.

items.items: The nutrients that are consumed in the largest quantities and used for energy, growth and body functions by living organisms.
Assessment of protein of an individual.
Assessment of carbohydrates of an individual.
Assessment of conditionally essential amino acids are these sinthetized in human organism (not essential), but they are used more faster then produced.
Assessment of essential amino acids of an individual.
Assessment of not essential amino acids of an individual.
Assessment of aspartic acid amino acid.
Histidine is a type of essential amino acids.
Isoleucine is a type of essential amino acids.
Assessment of Leucine is a type of essential amino acids.
Assessment of dietary fatty acids of an individual.
Assessment of dietary saturated fatty acids of an individual.
Assessment of dietary monounsaturated fatty acids (n-9) of an individual.
Assessment of cis-vaccenic acid is a type of monousaturated fatty acids.
Assessment of polyunsaturated acids which include the n-6 fatty acids and n-3 fatty acids.
Measurement of n-3 fatty acids of an individual.
Assessment of linoleic acid of an individual.
Assessment of dietary trans fatty acids.
Assessment of sugars (1-2 degree of polymerization) of an individual.
Assessment of oligosaccharides (They have 3-9 degree of polymerization of an individual).
Assessment of polysaccharides (They have more than 9 degree of polymerization).
Assessment of monosaccharides (simple carbohydrate) of an individual.
Assessment of disaccharides (carbohydrate constitued by two units of monossacharides).
Assessment of maltodextrina is a type of sugar of an individual.
Assessment of fruit-oligosaccharides (FOS) is a type of sugar.
Measurement of starch, which is a complex carbohydrate and main energy reserve in plants, is present in grains, legumes, tubers, fruits, and root vegetables.
Assessment of non-starch polysaccharides which are also known as dietary fiber.
Assessment of starch-resistant is a type of sugar.
Assessment of hydrocolloids is a type of sugar.
